properties.areaDesc: Waupaca, WI; Shawano, WI; Outagamie, WI
properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 2 at 8:56AM CST until January 7 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...The National Weather Service in Green Bay WI has issued a Flood
Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin...

Wolf River near Shiocton affecting Shawano, Outagamie and Waupaca
Counties.

For the Lower Wolf River...including Shiocton...Minor flooding is
forecast.

The National Weather Service in Green Bay has issued a

* Flood Warning for
the Wolf River near Shiocton.
* From late tonight to Tuesday morning.
* At 7:30 AM CST Thursday the stage was 10.7 feet.
* Flood stage is 11.0 feet.
* Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage just
after midnight tonight to a crest of 11.2 feet early tomorrow
afternoon. It will then fall below flood stage early Monday
morning.
* Impact...At 11.0 feet, There is minor flooding in the Shiocton
area including the city park and boat landing.
* Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 11.2
feet on 04/23/2003.
properties.instruction:
Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive
cars through flooded areas.

Caution is urged when walking near riverbanks.

Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.

Additional information is available at www.weather.gov.

The next statement will be issued this evening by 900 PM CST.
